'''Addanki Dayakar''' is an Indian political activist and important leader with [[Telangana Joint Action Committee]].<ref>[http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/andhra_pradesh/Parties-Sweat-It-Out-at-Night-as-T-Nominations-Close-Today/2014/04/09/article2158076.ece Parties Sweat It Out at Night as T Nominations Close Today - The New Indian Express<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He is also the president of Telangana Mala Mahanadu.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/four-jac-members-in-congress-list-of-110-assembly-seats/article5877038.ece Four JAC members in Congress list of 110 Assembly seats - The Hindu<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==Early life==
He was born in Nuthankal mandal [[Nalgonda district]] in [[Andhra pradesh]]. He graduated MCA and  LLB from [[Osmania University]].

==Career==
He is a major proponent of [[Telangana statehood]]. He joined Congress party in March 2014 and unsuccessfully contested [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly election, 2014]] from Tungaturthi assembly constituency.<ref>[http://indianexpress.com/article/india/politics/kcr-joins-ls-contest-from-medak-to-teach-cong-a-lesson/ KCR joins LS contest from Medak to teach Cong a ‘lesson’ | The Indian Express<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140409/nation-politics/article/congress-flip-flop-telangana-students Congress flip-flop on Telangana students<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/andhra_pradesh/Congress-TRS-Launch-Charm-Offensive-to-Hijack-TJAC/2014/03/17/article2113351.ece#.U0atvLZdVfY Congress, TRS Launch Charm Offensive to Hijack TJAC - The New Indian Express<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

