{{Infobox company | name = American Pie Council | logo = File:American_Pie_Council_logo.jpg | type = | foundation = | location_city = Lake Forest, Illinois<ref name=bbw/> | location_country = USA | key_people = Linda Hoskins, Executive Director<ref name=bbw/> | industry = | num_employees = | homepage = {{URL|piecouncil.org}} }} The '''American Pie Council''' ('''APC''') is an organization committed to "preserving America's [[pie]] heritage and promoting America's love affair with pies".<ref name=APC1>{{cite web |url=http://www.piecouncil.org/Membership/Join |title=Who We Are |work=American Pie Council website |accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> As America's only purely pie-focused national organization,<ref name=yahoo>{{cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/american-pie-councils-survey-gives-150000743.html |title=American Pie Council's Survey Gives a Taste of Country’s Relationship With an All-American Dessert Celebrated on National Pie Day, Jan. 23 |author=American Pie Council |date=January 15, 2014 |work=Yahoo Finance |accessdate=January 23, 2014 |quote=The American Pie Council is the only organization committed to maintaining America’s pie heritage... |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219134720/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/american-pie-councils-survey-gives-150000743.html |archivedate=February 19, 2014 |df= }}</ref> the APC combines aspects of a [[Club (organization)#Hobby club|hobby club]], [[professional association]], [[trade group]], and pro-pie [[interest group]].<ref name=bbw>{{cite web |url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=4204731 |title=Company Overview of The American Pie Council |author= |date= |work=Bloomberg Businessweek |accessdate=January 23, 2014 |quote=The American Pie Council provides personal, professional, and commercial memberships to pie lovers. The company allows consumer members to exchange recipes, in-store coupons, and ideas, as well as commercial members to participate in a variety of network and promotional opportunities.}}</ref>
==Activities== The Council offers both personal and commercial memberships which allow individual participants to have discussions and swap recipes with fellow pie lovers, while providing commercial members with business networking opportunities and promotional support.<ref name=bbw/> The APC has run the APC National Pie Championships since 1995.<ref name=NPC14>{{cite web |url=http://www.piecouncil.org/Events/NationalPieChampionships |title=Announcing the 2014 APC National Pie Championships® |work=American Pie Council website |accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> The event is usually held in [[Celebration, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment/restaurants/os-heather-mcpherson-pie-festival-20130419,0,2160207.column |title=A slice of life: Celebration's American Pie Festival |author=Heather McPherson |date=April 25, 2013 |work=Orlando Sentinel |accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> The competition is open to amateur, professional, and commercial bakers. As an example of typical categories, the categories at the 2014 competition were:<ref name=NPC14/> {{div col|colwidth=30em}} *[[Apple pie|Apple]] *[[Blueberry pie|Blueberry]] *Chocolate *Citrus *[[Cream pie|Cream]] *Cream Cheese *Comstock/Wilderness (Apple, Cherry, Blueberry, Strawberry, Combination 2+ flavors) *Fruit/Berry *Innovation *[[Key lime pie|Key Lime]] *Nut *Paramount Peach *Peanut Butter *[[Pumpkin pie|Pumpkin]] *Special Dietary (gluten free, no sugar added) *Open Competition {{div col end}}
The APC also sponsors or promotes other pie-centric events throughout the year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.piecouncil.org/Events/MoreHappenings |title=Happenings in the Pie World 2014 |work=American Pie Council website |accessdate=January 24, 2014}}</ref> The APC council also conducts surveys of pie consumption. APC research has shown that Apple is Americans' favorite pie, that 59% of Americans consider pie an appropriate late-night snack, and that 20% of Americans have eaten an entire pie.<ref name=funfacts>{{cite web |url=http://www.piecouncil.org/pdf/Pie_Fun_Facts.pdf |title=Pie Fun Facts |publisher=American Pie Council |accessdate=January 24, 2014}}</ref>
=== National Pie Day === [[File:National Pie Day 2014 poster.jpg|thumb|2014 National Pie Day/''Labor Day'' tie-in poster]] National Pie Day, which is held annually on January 23, is now sponsored by the APC since 1986.<ref name=APC1/> The holiday was started in the mid-1970s by Boulder, Colorado teacher [[Charlie Papazian]]<ref name=denverpost>{{cite web | url = http://www.denverpost.com/lifestyles/ci_24976278/national-pie-day-colorado-born-holiday | title = National Pie Day: A Colorado-born holiday | date = January 23, 2014 | work = [[The Denver Post]]}}</ref> after he declared his birthday to be National Pie Day.<ref name=dallasnews>{{cite web | url = http://www.dallasnews.com/news/local-news/20110121-sunday-is-national-pie-day-when-pie-takes-center-stage.ece | title = Sunday is National Pie Day, when pie takes center stage | first = Eric | last = Aasen | date = January 21, 2012 | work = [[The Dallas Morning News]]}}</ref> This should not be confused with [[Pi Day]] which the U.S. Congress recognizes as March 14.
In 2014, the APC partnered with [[Paramount Pictures]] in promoting the romantic thriller film ''[[Labor Day (film)|Labor Day]]'' in conjunction with National Pie Day.<ref name=variety>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/labor-day-national-pie-day-1201059145/ |title='Labor Day' Partners with American Pie Council for National Pie Day |date=January 15, 2014 |work=Variety |accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref> (A pie-making scene features prominently in the film, and the film's general release was within a few days of National Pie Day.)
The APC distributed a promotional poster to pie shops and bakeries featuring images of the film's stars [[Kate Winslet]], [[Josh Brolin]], and [[Gattlin Griffith]] in the pie-making scene. ''[[New York Post]]'' writer Lou Lumenick noted dryly that the scene was an "eccentric choice for a promotion" since Brolin's character is an escaped murderer and "before they all make pies together, he abducts them from a supermarket and ties both of them up... A bond does emerge between Brolin and his hostages before he surrenders to police. But still." The poster is captioned in part "It makes the time we spend together, just a little sweeter. Pie. Grab a slice of life."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2014/01/15/poster-celebrates-make-a-pie-with-a-murderer-day/ |title=Poster celebrates 'Make a Pie With a Murderer Day' |author=Lou Lumenick |date=January 15, 2014 |work=New York Post |accessdate=January 23, 2014}}</ref>
(Notwithstanding any problematic overtones, though, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'''s take on the scene was "What damage [the 1999 film] ''[[American Pie (film)|American Pie]]'' did for the pie industry, ''Labor Day'' has reversed.")<ref name=variety/>
