{{Infobox language |name=Matagalpa |states=[[Nicaragua]] |region=Central Highlands |extinct=c. 1875 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Misumalpan languages|Misumalpan]] |fam2=[[Sumalpan languages|Sumalpan]] |fam3=[[Matagalpan languages|Matagalpan]] |iso3=mtn |glotto=mata1288 |glottorefname=Matagalpa }}
'''Matagalpa''' is an extinct [[Misumalpan]] language formerly spoken in the central highlands of [[Nicaragua]]. The language became extinct in the nineteenth century, and only few short wordlists remain. It was closely related to [[Cacaopera language|Cacaopera]]. The ethnic group, which numbers about 20,000, now speaks [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
