The '''Slovenian Red Cross''' ({{lang-sl|Rdeči križ Slovenije}}) is a [[non-government organisation|non-government]] and [[non-profit organisation|non-profit]] [[humanitarian organisation]], part of the [[International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement]]. It was established in [[Gradac, Metlika|Gradac]] in June 1944,<ref name="RKD13676">{{cite web|url=http://giskd2s.situla.org/rkd/Opis.asp?Esd=13676 |title=13676: Gradac - Hiša Gradac 55 |trans-title=13676: Gradac – House Gradac No. 55 |work=Register nepremične kulturne dediščine [Registry of Immovable Cultural Heritage] |publisher=Ministrstvo za kulturo Republike Slovenije |language=Slovenian|accessdate=26 July 2013}}</ref> at first as part of the [[Yugoslav Red Cross]]. It became an independent entity after the [[Slovenia]]n proclamation of independence in 1991. It has its headquarters in [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia.  

